A train has allegedly caught fire in the Braamfontein area. * Editor's note: This is a developing story. We will bring you updates as more information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - A Metrorail train has allegedly caught fire in Braamfontein, Johannesburg. Gauteng Metrorail spokesperson Lillian Mofokeng said it is not clear how the fire started. "I can confirm that there a train that is on fire in the Braamfontein area, near Park Station. "It is not clear how many trains are affected by the fire but we are on our way to the scene to investigate", said Mofokeng.